      <description>
        
        
        &lt;p&gt;These Regulations govern your access to and use of the Website, Application, and Services (collectively, the “Services”) provided by Cordis, under KSF Cybersecurity Initative, under LVMLabs (“we,” “us,” or “our”). By using the Services associated, you agree to be bound by these Regulations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Legal&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;legal&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#legal&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3&gt;SECTION 230 LIMITATION OF LIABILITY &amp;amp; CONTENT DISCLAIMER&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;section-230-limitation-of-liability--content-disclaimer&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#section-230-limitation-of-liability--content-disclaimer&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Pursuant to Section 230 of the Communications Decency Act of 1996 (47 U.S.C. § 230), Cordis and LVMLabs operates strictly as an &amp;ldquo;interactive computer service&amp;rdquo; provider and shall not be treated as the publisher or speaker of any information provided by another information content provider.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cordis and LVMLabs expressly disclaims any and all liability arising from, or relating to, user-generated content, texts, messages, media, or transmissions hosted on or communicated through this platform. All users are solely, exclusively, and legally liable for the content they transmit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Under federal law, Cordis and LVMLabs is immune from liability for any defamatory, offensive, unlawful, or otherwise actionable material posted by third parties. The reservation of our right to monitor, moderate, or remove content at our sole discretion shall not be construed as an assumption of liability, nor does it waive any immunities provided under 47 U.S.C. § 230.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Terms of Service&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;terms-of-service&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#terms-of-service&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3&gt;ACCEPTANCE&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;acceptance&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#acceptance&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;By accessing or using any part of the Services, you agree to comply with and be bound by these Terms. If you are using the Services on behalf of an organization, you represent that you have the authority to bind that organization to these Terms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;USAGE&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;usage&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#usage&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;You are strictly prohibited from using the Service to transmit, post, link to, or otherwise distribute any content that falls under the following categories:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Illegal Content &amp;amp; Activities:&lt;/strong&gt; Any material that violates federal, state, or local laws. This includes, but is not limited to, the sale or promotion of illegal drugs, unauthorized weapons, human trafficking, or instructions on creating explosives or executing cyberattacks.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Threats &amp;amp; Harassment:&lt;/strong&gt; Direct or indirect threats of violence, physical harm, or death against any individual or group. This includes targeted harassment, stalking, cyberbullying, and doxxing (the unauthorized release of private, personally identifiable information).&lt;br&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Intellectual Property Infringement:&lt;/strong&gt; Any content that infringes upon third-party copyrights, trademarks, patents, trade secrets, or proprietary rights.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Malicious Software &amp;amp; Interference:&lt;/strong&gt; The transmission of viruses, malware, spyware, ransomware, or any code designed to disrupt, damage, or limit the functionality of this platform or any user&amp;rsquo;s device.&lt;br&gt;
